    "summary": "Kokoro-82M is a single-workload feed-forward TTS model (phonemes -> 24 kHz speech), not multi-modal: one shared TTNN pipeline in tt/pipeline.py (build_pipeline + run_tts) chains ~20 'graduated' native ttnn stubs (PLBERT text encoder -> duration/prosody predictor -> alignment -> F0/N -> decoder -> ISTFTNet/NSF generator). Both the demo and tests import this single pipeline. Two near-identical dedicated perf tests exist (tests/e2e/test_tts_perf.py which self-opens its device like the demo, and tests/e2e/test_main_perf.py which uses the pytest device fixture); both profile the same one forward pass and assert perf only (no PCC). The end-to-end correctness gate is tests/e2e/test_e2e_tts.py, which enforces a log-magnitude-spectrogram PCC >= 0.95 (SPEC_PCC_TARGET) plus exact duration match and Gate-2 module-invocation coverage. Reviewer note: the e2e test intentionally does NOT gate raw-waveform PCC (only prints it) because the NSF vocoder is chaotically F0-phase sensitive \u2014 the gated metric is the phase-invariant spectrogram PCC at 0.95. Per-component PCC tests under tests/pcc/ each gate at 0.99. Many _stubs also have .best_native/.last_good_native/.preiter_native sidecar snapshots (not source); the runnable decoder/generator are hand-wired in pipeline.py rather than via _stubs/decoder.py and _stubs/generator.py.",
